article.headline: Arkansas St. 71, New Orleans 56
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. -- Donald Boone scored 20 points, and Arkansas State held New Orleans without a field goal for over 12 minutes in a 71-56 win Saturday night. The Red Wolves (10-4, 2-1 Sun Belt) didn't allow a field goal for the final 10:04 of the first half and the first 2:08 of the second. Kyndall Dykes and T.J. Worley scored 15 points each for New Orleans (6-8, 2-2). New Orleans led by nine in the first half before its extended offensive slump. Arkansas State was ahead 25-24 at the half, then steadily built its lead in the second. The Red Wolves only missed seven shots of any kind in the second half, going 10-of-13 from the field and 23-of-27 from the free throw line.
